Distribution. Known from the Alas River drainage in northern Sumatra, which drains the eastern face of the Leuser Mountain Range and the western face of the Central Gajo Mountain Range, debouching into the Indian Ocean (
Fig. 3
).

Etymology. This species is named after its type locality, the Ketambe research station, which is world renowned as a site for the study of the Sumatran orangutan (
Pongo abelii
). Used as a noun in apposition.
